verses.text: O give thanks unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*; for \add he is\add* good : because his mercy \add endureth\add* for ever. \q1
Let Israel now say , that his mercy \add endureth\add* for ever. \q1
Let the house of Aaron now say , that his mercy \add endureth\add* for ever. \q1
Let them now that fear the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* say , that his mercy \add endureth\add* for ever. \q1

I called upon the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3050"\+w*
d* in distress : the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3050"\+w*
d* answered me, \add and set me\add* in a large place.  +  r 118.5  t in distress: Heb. out of distress * \q1
The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add is\add* on my side; I will not fear : what can man do unto me?\f + \fr 118.6 \ft on…: Heb. for me\f* \q1
The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* taketh my part with them that help me: therefore shall I see \add my desire\add* upon them that hate me. \q1
\add It is\add* better to trust in the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* than to put confidence in man. \q1
\add It is\add* better to trust in the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* than to put confidence in princes. \q1
All nations compassed me about : but in the name of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* will I destroy them.\f + \fr 118.10 \ft destroy…: Heb. cut them off\f* \q1
They compassed me about ; yea, they compassed me about : but in the name of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* I will destroy them. \q1

They compassed me about like bees ; they are quenched as the fire of thorns : for in the name of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* I will destroy them.\f + \fr 118.12 \ft destroy: Heb. cut down\f* \q1
Thou hast thrust sore at me that I might fall : but the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* helped me. \q1
The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3050"\+w*\nd* \add is\add* my strength and song , and is become my salvation. \q1
The voice of rejoicing and salvation \add is\add* in the tabernacles of the righteous : the right hand of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* doeth valiantly. \q1

The right hand of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* is exalted : the right hand of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* doeth valiantly. \q1
I shall not die , but live , and declare the works of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3050"\+w*\nd*. \q1
The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3050"\+w*\nd* hath chastened me sore : but he hath not given me over unto death. \b \q1
Open to me the gates of righteousness : I will go into them, \add and\add* I will praise the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3050"\+w*\nd*: \q1
This gate of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, into which the righteous shall enter. \q1
I will praise thee: for thou hast heard me, and art become my salvation. \q1
The stone \add which\add* the builders refused is become the head \add stone\add* of the corner. \q1
This is the \nd \+w LORD’s|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* doing; it \add is\add* marvellous in our eyes.\f + \fr 118.23 \ft the \+nd LORD’s\+nd*…: Heb. from the \+nd LORD\+nd*\f* \q1
This \add is\add* the day \add which\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath made ; we will rejoice and be glad in it. \q1

Save now, I beseech thee, O 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*: O 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, I beseech thee, send now prosperity. \q1

Blessed \add be\add* he that cometh in the name of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*: we have blessed you out of the house of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*. \q1
God \add is\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, which hath shewed us light : bind the sacrifice with cords , \add even\add* unto the horns of the altar. \q1
Thou \add art\add* my God , and I will praise thee: \add thou art\add* my God , I will exalt thee. \q1
O give thanks unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*; for \add he is\add* good : for his mercy \add endureth\add* for ever.
